      "writtenOn": "2017-11-15T17:51:32Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "this assumes that the caller is OK with a bogus URL. Better not to assume that.\n\nAlso if an app returns an invalid link to itself, a user may think that the app is not consistent with itself (not good)\n\nPlease return something so that a caller of this function can tell whether the URL generation succeed or not. It could be \"\" or \n\n  const InvalidBuildIDURL \u003d \"#invalid-build\"\n\nI believe a fragment link is a typical approach for such cases. E.g HTML sanitizers do that (e.g. Gitiles does that and a security engineer suggested that when I was implementing an HTML sanitizer).",
      "parentUuid": "f7a27dcc_11dd70e9",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 36,
        "startChar": 3,
        "endLine": 36,
        "endChar": 58
      },
